Great. Here is the detailed, step-by-step walkthrough of how a game of Three-Dragon Ante would ideally be played on Discord.

Three-Dragon Ante: Step-by-Step Discord Gameplay
This walkthrough describes the ideal gameplay flow from a player's perspective, assuming all game rules and bot features are fully implemented and functional.

Phase 0: Game Creation & Lobby (Public Channel)
This is the only part of the game that takes place in a public channel.

Creating the Game:

A player types !3da or !tda in a designated channel.
Bot Response (Public): The bot creates a new public message with an interactive embed.
Title: "Three-Dragon Ante Lobby"
Players: Lists the user who created the game.
Status: "Waiting for players..."
Buttons: Join, Leave, Start Game, Cancel Game.
Dropdown Menu: "Select D&D Special Abilities (Optional)". The options are Bluff, Concentration, Diplomacy, Intimidate, etc.
Joining and Setup:

Other players click the Join button. The "Players" list in the embed updates automatically.
Any player in the lobby can select a D&D Special Ability from the dropdown. The bot confirms their choice with an ephemeral message visible only to them (e.g., "You have selected the Concentration ability.").
The game creator is the only one who can see and use the Start Game and Cancel Game buttons.
Starting the Game:

Once at least two players have joined, the creator clicks Start Game.
Bot Response (Public): The lobby embed is updated to a final state.
Title: "Three-Dragon Ante: Game In Progress"
Status: "The game has started! Check your DMs to play."
The buttons and dropdown menu are removed.
Bot Action (Backend): The bot initializes the game state. Each player is given 50 gold and a hand of 6 cards from the shuffled deck. It then sends the first private message.
Phase 1: Game Start & Pre-Gambit Setup (DMs)
From this point forward, all interactions happen in private DMs between each player and the bot.

Receive Initial Hand:

Bot Message (DM to each player):
"Welcome to Three-Dragon Ante! Here is your starting hand and gold."
Embed:
Title: "Your Hand"
Content: A clear, visual list of the 6 cards in your hand, ideally with their strength and an image for each.
Footer: "Your Hoard: 50 Gold"
Optional Card Drafting Phase:

(This assumes the drafting variant is enabled for the game.)
Bot Message (DM to the starting player):
"This game includes a card draft. 20 optional cards have been added to the deck. You and your opponents will take turns removing 10 of them."
Embed: Displays the 20 optional cards.
Action: A dropdown menu lists all 20 cards. The player selects one to remove.
This process repeats, rotating through players, until 10 cards have been removed. The bot sends a DM to the active player on their turn. A final summary DM is sent to all players listing the 10 cards that were removed from the game.
Phase 2: The Gambit Begins - Ante (DMs)
Choose Ante Card:

Bot Message (DM to each player):
"A new gambit begins! Choose a card from your hand to ante."
Embed: Shows your current hand.
Action: A dropdown menu containing your cards.
Player Action: You select a card from the dropdown. The bot confirms your choice with a quick message update (e.g., "You have anted the Red Dragon.").
Ante Resolution:

Once all players have selected their ante card, the bot processes the results and sends a summary to everyone.
Bot Message (DM to each player):
Embed Title: "Gambit 1: Ante Results"
Content:
"All players have anted. Here are the revealed cards:"
A list shows each player and the card they anted (e.g., "You anted Red Dragon (Str 10)", "Opponent anted The Fool (Str 3)").
"The highest strength is 10. All players pay 10 gold to the stakes."
"Your opponent played the highest unique strength card and is the leader for the first round."
Game State Update:
"Your Hoard: 40 Gold"
"Stakes: 20 Gold" (in a 2-player game)
"Ante Cards on Table: Red Dragon (Str 10), The Fool (Str 3)"
Phase 3: The Gambit - Playing Rounds (DMs)
A gambit consists of at least three rounds.

Leader's Turn:

The bot messages the current leader.
Bot Message (DM to Leader):
"It's your turn to play. You are the leader."
Embed: A full game state summary.
Your Hand & Hoard: Lists your cards and current gold.
Your Flight: Shows cards you've played this gambit (empty on round 1).
Opponent Flights: Shows the cards in each opponent's flight and their hoard size.
Game Info: Current stakes amount, Ante cards on the table.
Action: A dropdown menu to choose a card to play.
Player Action: The leader selects a card. Let's say they play Green Dragon (Str 8).
Play Resolution (Leader):

The bot processes the play and sends an update to all players.
Bot Message (DM to all players):
Embed Title: "Gambit 1, Round 1"
Content:
"Opponent (Leader) played Green Dragon (Str 8)."
"The card's power triggers: The opponent to your left chooses either to give you a weaker evil dragon from his or her hand or to pay you 5 gold."
A sub-message explains the outcome: "You chose to pay 5 gold."
Updated Game State (in the same embed): A refreshed view of all player flights and hoards.
Next Player's Turn:

The bot now messages the next player in order.
Bot Message (DM to current player):
"It's your turn to play. The previous card was Green Dragon (Str 8). Your card's power will trigger if its strength is 8 or less."
Embed: The same full game state summary.
Action: A dropdown menu to choose a card.
Player Action: You play Silver Dragon (Str 6).
Play Resolution (Non-Leader) & Special Flights:

The bot processes the play. Because 6 <= 8, the power triggers.
Bot Message (DM to all players):
Embed Title: "Gambit 1, Round 1"
Content:
"You played Silver Dragon (Str 6). Its power triggers!"
"Power: Each player with at least one good dragon in his or her flight draws a card. You and Opponent both draw one card."
(If applicable) "Special Flight! You played your third Silver Dragon, completing a Color Flight! All opponents pay you 6 gold."
Updated Game State: Shows updated flights, hoards, and hand sizes.
End of Round Info: "The round is over. Opponent played the strongest card (8 vs 6) and will be the leader for Round 2."
Buying Cards:

If a player starts their turn with one or zero cards, the bot handles this automatically.
Bot Message (DM to that player): "You have only one card left. You must buy new cards. The top card of the deck is a Brass Dragon (Str 5). You pay 5 gold to the stakes and draw until you have four cards in hand."
Phase 4: End of Gambit & Drawing New Cards (DMs)
Determining the Winner:

After Round 3 ends (assuming no ties for strongest flight):
Bot Message (DM to all players):
Embed Title: "Gambit 1 Over"
Content:
"After 3 rounds, the gambit is over."
"Final Flight Strength: You (22), Opponent (19)."
"You win the gambit and take the 35 gold from the stakes!"
Updated Game State: Shows everyone's new, final gold total for the gambit.
Drawing New Cards:

Bot Message (DM to all players, can be part of the previous message):
"All flights and ante cards are discarded. Each player draws two new cards."
A new embed follows immediately, showing each player their new hand and updated gold total, ready for the next gambit's ante phase.
Phase 5: Game End (Public Channel)
Triggering the End:

The game ends when, at the conclusion of a gambit, at least one player has 0 gold.
Final Announcement:

Bot Message (DM to all players): "Your opponent has run out of gold! The game is over."
Bot Response (Public Channel - updating the original lobby message):
Title: "Three-Dragon Ante: Game Over!"
Embed Content:
"The game has concluded!"
"Winner: You!"
Final Standings:
You: 100 Gold
Opponent: 0 Gold
The bot then cleans up the game session.